  "body": "### Description\n\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\n*Type*: Bug\n*Summary*: for now you can navigate to wallet screen easily from chat screen and back and in case when on both tabs wallet screens (\"Send Transaction\", \"New request\") are shown it can cause some navigation glitches that mostly lead to replacing user input on other tab.\n\n### Reproduction\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\nPrerequisites: user have User A and User B in contacts and some amount of ETH / tokens in wallet\n#### Scenario 1:\n1) open 1-1 chat with User A\n2) /send ETHro 0.0001\n3) Switch to the wallet on \"Send Transaction\" screen\n4) Tap on Send -> choose another recipient (User B)\n5) Try to specify the amount. \n**Actual result:** The amount is not editable.\n**Expected result:** can edit the amount.\n6) Go back to Chats screen. \n**Actual result:**  Amount of transaction is erased and the recipient is replaced to User B. Close screen.\n**Expected result:**  all data is preserved\n7) Close \"Send transaction\" screen.\n7) Go back to wallet screen again. \n**Actual result:**   Send Transaction screen contains only empty recipient and Amount fields. The only way to proceed - start all from scratch.\n**Expected result:**  all data is preserved\n![img_e3339df9f6f9-1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/53738314-2b58dc00-3e8f-11e9-844e-d98b5997bc04.jpeg)\n\nThat's working in both ways, so if you are sending transaction from wallet and, then go to chat and here using send commands - all your data on \"Send transaction\" screen in \"Wallet\" tab will be replaced accordingly to data from /send command.\n\n#### Scenario 2:\n1) Go to wallet -> Receive\n2) Tap on \"Send Transaction\" request\n3) Specify amount\n4) Specify recipient\n5) go to chat and send ETH to any user ( using /send command) \n6) Go back to wallet. Recipient is erased.\n7) Enter new recipient and tap on send request. Go to wallet tab. Now all values are preserved.\n\n\n\n### Additional Information\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\n* Status version: release 0.10.0, nightly 04.03.2019\n\n* Operating System: Android, IOS",
